50|$|The use {{of ammonia}} <b>smelling</b> <b>salts</b> to revive people injured during sport is not {{recommended}} because it may inhibit or delay a proper and thorough neurological assessment by a healthcare professional, such as after concussions when hospitalization may be advisable, and some governing bodies recommend specifically against it. The irritant nature of <b>smelling</b> <b>salts</b> means that they can exacerbate any pre-existing cervical spine injury by causing reflex withdrawal away from them.|$|R
